        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 9:40PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 940 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Pocola, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Alma...                           Shibley...
Dyer...                           Kibler...
Central City...                   Cameron...
Pocola...                         Rye Hill...
Moffett...                        Fort Smith...
Fort Smith Regional Airport...    Van Buren...
Rudy...                           Scullyville...
Hackett...                        Concord...
Arkoma...                         Braden...
Figure Five...                    Mill Creek...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 0 and 18.
Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 326 and 328.
Interstate 540 between mile markers 1 and 14.
Interstate 49 between mile markers 22 and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
